HEADWORD: Endlong
<hw>End"long`</hw> <pr>(?; 115)</pr>, <pos>adv. & prep.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Along</er>.]</ety> <def>Lengthwise; along.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The doors were all of adamants eterne,⟦br⟧
I-clenched overthwart and <qex>endelong</qex>⟦br⟧
With iron tough.</q> <rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He pricketh <qex>endelong</qex> the large space.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To thrust the raft <qex>endlong</qex> across the moat.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Endmost</ent>⟦br⟧
